title: 820-4924 bios
message:
Another shop sent me an 820-4924 that they tried to flash the bios on but failed. The chip was missing so I pulled one off a donor board and put it in my TL866 to program with a new ME region. However, once I dumped it it looks like junk -- no serial number or "hwc" anywhere.

Does anybody have a clean 820-4924 bios? Or is this normal for the new boards?

Dump: [url]https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BwIAaoowgCg6VXZIRU5lbjVoOE0/view?usp=sharing[/url]

title: 820-4924 bios
message: Nothing wrong with that dump Serial is C02PWK0BFVH3. Just use a clean ME and ready to go.

title: 820-4924 bios
message: Worked great, thanks. Not sure why I couldn't find the serial earlier.
